VALERIE JARRETT was President Barack Obama’s longest serving senior adviser, with responsibility for criminal justice and police reform. In the wake of the killing of George Floyd and protests across the country, Anne McElvoy asks whether this moment could be a turning point on racial equality in America, and which changes to policing would be most effective. Also, how does the outcry affect President Donald Trump’s chances of reelection—and how does Ms Jarrett assess Joe Biden’s record on race? Runtime: 37 min  Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn Please subscribe to The Economist for full access to print, digital and audio editions: www.economist.com/podcastoffer